access_key.name: Description
access_key.value:
The access key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

dynamodb_endpoint.name: Description
dynamodb_endpoint.value:
Use this to override the default endpoint URL constructed from the `region`.
It's typically used to connect to dynamodb-local.

ec2.name: Description
ec2.value: Use this to override the default endpoint URL constructed from the `region`.

elb.name: Description
elb.value: Use this to override the default endpoint URL constructed from the `region`.

iam.name: Description
iam.value: Use this to override the default endpoint URL constructed from the `region`.

insecure.name: Description
insecure.value: Explicitly allow the provider to perform "insecure" SSL requests. If omitted,default value is `false`

kinesis_endpoint.name: Description
kinesis_endpoint.value:
Use this to override the default endpoint URL constructed from the `region`.
It's typically used to connect to kinesalite.

max_retries.name: Description
max_retries.value:
The maximum number of times an AWS API request is
being executed. If the API request still fails, an error is
thrown.

profile.name: Description
profile.value:
The profile for API operations. If not set, the default profile
created with `aws configure` will be used.

region.name: Description
region.value:
The region where AWS operations will take place. Examples
are us-east-1, us-west-2, etc.

secret_key.name: Description
secret_key.value:
The secret key for API operations. You can retrieve this
from the 'Security & Credentials' section of the AWS console.

shared_credentials_file.name: Description
shared_credentials_file.value:
The path to the shared credentials file. If not set
this defaults to ~/.aws/credentials.

token.name: Description
token.value:
session token. A session token is only required if you are
using temporary security credentials.

block_device.name: Removed
block_device.value: Split out into three sub-types; see Changelog and Docs

subnet_id.name: Deprecated
subnet_id.value: Attribute subnet_id is deprecated on network_acl resources. Use subnet_ids instead

type.name: Description
type.value: Type of rule, ingress (inbound) or egress (outbound).
